Definition: an Old Testament book lamenting the desolation of Judah after the destruction of Jerusalem in 586 BC
Example: traditionally attributed to the prophet Jeremiah
Synonyms: Book_of_Lamentations, book, i, Writings, p, Old_Testament, an, Old, Testament, lamenting, the, desolation, of, Judah, after, destruction, Jerusalem, in, BC, traditionally, attributed, to, prophet, Jeremiah
Category: noun.communication
